'''Ronnie Cowan''' is a [[Scottish National Party]] (SNP) politician. He has been the [[Member of Parliament]] (MP) for [[Inverclyde (UK Parliament constituency)|Inverclyde]] since the [[United Kingdom general election, 2015|2015 general election]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Cowan|first1=Ronnie|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/politics/constituencies/S14000038|website=BBC Web|title= Inverclyde Parliamentary Constituency|publisher=BBC|accessdate=8 May 2015}}</ref>

He is the son of [[Greenock Morton F.C.|Morton]] and [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] football goalkeeper [[Jimmy Cowan (footballer)|Jimmy Cowan]].<ref>[http://www.snp.org/people/ronnie-cowan SNP profile] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518082919/http://www.snp.org/people/ronnie-cowan |date=18 May 2015 }}</ref> Cowan is from Greenock, and was educated at [[Greenock Academy]]. He is an owner of an IT service company.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Nutt|first1=Kathleen|title=Meet your new Scottish MPs: #38 Ronnie Cowan, Inverclyde|url=http://www.thenational.scot/politics/meet-your-new-scottish-mps-38-ronnie-cowan-inverclyde.5819|accessdate=22 October 2015|publisher=The National}}</ref>

