{{italic title}} '''''Vremya Novostei''''' ({{lang-ru|Время новостей}}, translated as ''News Time'') was a Russian business socio-political daily [[newspaper]] based in [[Moscow]].
''Vremya Novostei'' was founded in 2000 by former ''Vremya MN'' newspaper journalists led by editor-in-chief Vladimir Gurevich retiring in consequence of the non-payment of wages.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://smi.ru/2000/03/15/953123974.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20010507115250/http://www.smi.ru/2000/03/15/953123974.html|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2001-05-07|script-title=ru:"Время новостей" - партийный орган СПС|publisher=SMI.ru|date=2000-03-15|language=Russian}}</ref> The first issue was published on March 16, 2000,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://lenta.ru/russia/2000/03/15/vremya/|script-title=ru:Газета "Время новостей" выходит в свет|publisher=[[Lenta.Ru]]|date=2000-03-15|accessdate=2009-05-14|language=Russian|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071009222632/http://www.lenta.ru/russia/2000/03/15/vremya/|archivedate=2007-10-09|df=}}</ref> and the last issue was published on December 17, 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://vremya.ru/2010/232/52/266602.html|script-title=ru:Уважаемые читатели!|publisher=Vremya Novostei|date=2010-12-17|language=Russian}}</ref>
In February 2011, ''Vremya Novostei'' was relaunched as ''[[Moskovskiye Novosti]]'', but ceased publication in February 2014.
